<p><i><b>No End in Sight</b></i> is a <a href="/wiki/2007_in_film" title="2007 in film">2007</a> <a href="/wiki/Documentary_film" title="Documentary film">documentary film</a> about the American <a href="/wiki/Iraq_War" title="Iraq War">occupation of Iraq</a>. The film marks the directorial debut of political scientist and former software entrepreneur <a href="/wiki/Charles_H._Ferguson" title="Charles H. Ferguson">Charles H. Ferguson</a>. The film premiered <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="2007-01-22"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="01-22"><a href="/wiki/January_22" title="January 22">January 22</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/2007" title="2007">2007</a></span> at the <a href="/wiki/2007_Sundance_Film_Festival" title="2007 Sundance Film Festival">2007 Sundance Film Festival</a>. The film opened in <a href="/wiki/Limited_release" title="Limited release">limited release</a> in the United States on <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="2007-07-27"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="07-27"><a href="/wiki/July_27" title="July 27">July 27</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/2007" title="2007">2007</a></span>, playing in 2 theaters. As of December 2007<sup class="plainlinks noprint asof-tag update" style="display:none;"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=No_End_in_Sight&amp;action=edit" class="external text" title="http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=No_End_in_Sight&amp;action=edit" rel="nofollow">[update]</a></sup>, the film had grossed $1.4 million, and had been released on DVD.<sup id="cite_ref-Reuters_0-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Reuters-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
